# Testing Rule

Every function in core/ must have a pytest test.

Tests must use realistic examples — ideally derived from actual BOQ/macro
fixture files in tests/fixtures/, not invented edge cases unless the real
data doesn't cover something important.

When fixing a bug: write a failing test that reproduces it first, then fix
the code, then confirm the test passes.

Do not change matching or pricing logic without updating or adding tests
that cover the change.
